This paper deals with learning Gaussian Graphical Models, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of feedback vertex sets (FVSs) in modeling social or flight networks, which falls under the category of network analysis and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes efficient algorithms for structure learning, which involves optimization and computational complexity analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of exact inference, which falls under the category of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category as well.
